The paper explores the theoretical properties of multi-winner approval voting, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The analysis involves modeling voter behavior and equilibrium outcomes, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also considers the impact of institutional features on election outcomes, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
